                    h3 Jessica
                    em Lead Stylist
                    div(id="jessbio",style="display:none;color:white")
                        strong Jessica has spent eighteen years growing her skills as a colorist, cutter, and updo artist. She has a background in education and platform work, working for industry innovators such as L’Oreal Professionnel. Jessica is driven by the belief that beauty, function, confidence, and self expression can be attainable for everyone. She utilizes her passion for art, fashion, and relationships to cultivate a professional one on one experience for each and every client. Her patience and good natured disposition provides an environment of trust, allowing clients to explore new ideas on their own terms. Classic or edgy, sophisticated or free spirited, Jessica will take you where you want to go!
            .col-xs-6.col-md-4#kim(style="padding:20px")
                center
                    div(style='background-image:url("images/kimba.png");background-size:cover;height:20.5em;width:20.5em;border:solid white 5px')
                    h3 Kim
                    em Lead Stylist
                    div(id="kimbio",style="display:none;color:white")
                        strong Kim brings “Beachy Boho” from Florida to Brooklyn. A hairstylist for 12 years, Kim was trained by Redken’s top educators through to becoming becoming a Redken Master Stylist. She trained at the Redken Exchange on Fifth Ave in New York and in Tampa, she worked behind the scenes with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers Cheerleaders, doing hair for game days, photo shoots and their swimsuit calendars. As part of Kim’s freelance work she is a hair and makeup artist for the Saks fifth Ave corporate offices, and works on sets for various commercials and photo shoots. “Im inspired by the diversity and energy that New York has to offer. I plan on making people beautiful one head at a time!”
                        
            .col-xs-6#christine(style="padding:20px")
                center
                    div(style='background-image:url("images/christine2.png");background-size:cover;height:20.5em;width:20.5em;border:solid white 5px')
                    h3 Christine
                    em Senior Stylist
                    div(id="chrstinebio",style="display:none;color:white")
                        strong Christine is a warm ray of sunshine hailing from the west coast with almost two decades experience behind the chair. She’s incredible at creating natural, wearable, breathtaking color by incorporating techniques unique to our salon. Her cuts use soft edges on crisp lines and are customized to each clients individual needs. What brings people back into Christine’s chair is her genuine warmth, which works in congruence with her skill.
            
            .col-xs-6#mary(style="padding:20px")
                center
                    div(style='background-image:url("images/mary1.png");background-size:cover;height:20.5em;width:20.5em;border:solid white 5px')
                    h3 Mary
                    em Senior Stylist
                    div(id="marybio",style="display:none;color:white")
                        strong Mary Crocker knew from a very young age she wanted to be a hairdresser, doing her first haircut at the age of 11 for her time crunched mother. She finds her inspiration in her surroundings: “What are people wearing on the streets from neighborhood to neighborhood? The city is a constantly evolving environment full of fresh inspiration”. For men, she’s inspired by GQ and Mad Men, crisp and clean. Mary has spent a great deal of time working with barbers to really develop her skills in this frequently neglected aspect of hairdressing. Specializing in “wake and shake” hair for her ladies, meaning natural, wearable hair. Its always a fun and first class experience in Mary’s office!
            .col-xs-6#jenni(style="padding:20px")
                center
                    div(style='background-image:url("images/jenni3.png");background-size:cover;height:20.5em;width:20.5em;border:solid white 5px')
